cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper deals with word embeddings, which are commonly used in Natural Language Processing (NLP) systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper evaluates different models, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of large corpora and the evaluation of word embeddings for specific tasks could also suggest cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques, which could make it relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
